                  </persName>
            . As I was going down Tottenham court-road on the 29th of June, about ten o'clock in the morning; I was followed by the prisoner and by another person; I wanted to get rid of them; I went into a public house; they followed me into the house; they sat down on each side of me; I had twelve shillings and upwards in my pocket; I am certain I had it safe when I went into the house, for I had bought some cheese just before and had looked at my money; the prisoner sat on that side of me where my pocket was; I found his hand in my pocket; I had him taken up; he then confessed he had stole my money, that he had bought a handkerchief with part of it, and that the other man had the rest.</p>
               <p>
            
